Package generellSim

Class EventQueue

java.lang.Object
generellSim.EventQueue
public class EventQueue extends Object
Manages the queue of events in the simulation, ensuring events are processed in chronological order.
Author:
Botzan Güzel, Sergij Wennströmm, Ludvig Lidén

  • Constructor Details

    • EventQueue

      public EventQueue()
      Constructs an empty event queue. No arguments are required as the constructor only initializes the list to hold the events.

  • Method Details

    • addEvent

      public void addEvent(Event e)
      Adds a new event to the queue if it has not already occurred. The queue is then sorted to ensure chronological order of events.
      Parameters:
      e - The event to be added.

    • getNextEvent

      public Event getNextEvent()
      Retrieves and removes the next event in the queue, if any.
      Returns:
      The next event, or null if the queue is empty.

    • isEmpty

      public boolean isEmpty()
      Checks if the event queue is empty.
      Returns:
      True if the queue is empty, false otherwise.
